#eNCA reporter Ronald Masinda follows the story. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Flood victims in the Eastern Cape will be provided with temporary shelter. Homes have been washed away and about 1,000 people have been displaced. READ: Shelter to be provided for KZN flood victims Some are currently taking shelter in community halls. Residents in the Eastern Cape are trying to rebuild following recent flash floods. Our reporter Ronald Masinda is on the ground and he spoke to government officials earlier. Officials are responding with temporarily units for displaced residents. #DStv403 #eNCA pic.twitter.com/q5C1ujzBM3